1️⃣ Vertical Scaling: Making your existing server BIGGER
        Real World Example:
            You run a call center with 1 employee handling calls.
            Calls increase → You upgrade that employee to a super-agent who can handle 10x more calls.
            Same person — just more capable.
            AWS Example:
            Before Traffic Increase:        After Traffic Increase:
            ┌─────────────────┐             ┌─────────────────────┐
            │   t2.micro      │    →        │   t2.large          │
            │   1 vCPU        │             │   2 vCPU            │
            │   1 GB RAM      │             │   8 GB RAM          │
            │   Low cost      │             │   Higher cost       │
            └─────────────────┘             └─────────────────────┘
                  (Scale Up ⬆️)
            Real AWS Use Case:
                    Your RDS database is slow
                    Scale from db.t2.micro → db.t2.large
                    Same database — just more powerful
=====================================================================================================
2️⃣ Horizontal Scaling: Adding MORE servers instead of making one bigger

              Real World Example:
                      You run a call center with 1 employee.
                      Calls increase → You hire 5 more employees.
                      More people handling calls simultaneously.
              AWS Example:
              Low Traffic:                    High Traffic:
              ┌──────────┐                   ┌──────────┐
              │  EC2 #1  │        →          │  EC2 #1  │
              └──────────┘                   └──────────┘
              (1 instance)                   ┌──────────┐
                                             │  EC2 #2  │
                                             └──────────┘
                                             ┌──────────┐
                                             │  EC2 #3  │
                                             └──────────┘
                                             (3 instances - ASG scaled out ✅)
              Real AWS Use Case:
                      Your e-commerce website gets 10x traffic during a sale
                      ASG automatically adds 10 more EC2 instances
                      After sale → ASG removes extra instances to save cost
======================================================================================================
3️⃣ High Availability: Running your application in MULTIPLE locations so it never goes down
            Real World Example:
                    You run a call center in New York and London.
                    New York office catches fire 🔥 → Calls automatically reroute to London.
                    Customers never notice anything went wrong.
            AWS Example:
            
                                Users
                                  │
                                  ▼
                        ELB (Load Balancer)
                                  │
                      ┌───────────┴───────────┐
                      │                       │
                  AZ-1 (ap-south-1a)      AZ-2 (ap-south-1b)
                  ┌──────────┐              ┌──────────┐
                  │  EC2 #1  │              │  EC2 #2  │
                  │  EC2 #2  │              │  EC2 #3  │
                  └──────────┘              └──────────┘
                      ✅ Running                ✅ Running
                      │
                  AZ-1 FAILS ❌
                      │
                  ELB reroutes → AZ-2 ✅
                  (Zero downtime!)
            Real AWS Use Case:
                    Your app runs in ap-south-1a and ap-south-1b
                    AWS has a power outage in ap-south-1a
                    ELB automatically routes all traffic to ap-south-1b
                    Users experience zero downtime ✅
================================================================================================================

              Vertical Scaling	        Horizontal Scaling	      High Availability
What	        Bigger server	            More servers	            Multiple locations
How	          Upgrade instance size	    Add more instances	      Multi-AZ deployment
AWS Service	  EC2 instance type change	ASG	                      ELB + Multi-AZ ASG
Goal	        More power	              More capacity	            No downtime
Limit	        Has a max limit ❌	      No limit ✅	              Depends on AZs
Cost	        High	                    Moderate	                Higher
Downtime	    Sometimes ❌	            No ✅	                    No ✅
Example	      t2.micro → t2.large	      1 EC2 → 10 EC2s	          AZ-1 fails → AZ-2 takes over
